headline: Here Are Thursday’s Top Wall Street Analyst Research Calls: AutoZone, BXP, Fiserv, Meta Platforms, PayPal, Salesforce, Toast and More
summary: Pre-Market Stock Futures: The futures are trading modestly higher on Thursday after a rollercoaster session on Wednesday, as stocks fell after the open on weak ADP data showing private-sector employment shed 32,000 jobs in November, the largest in 2-1/2 years. That didn’t last long, as bonds rallied on hopes of a rate cut next week ... headline: EQT (EQT): Revisiting Valuation After a Strong Year-to-Date Share Price Rebound
summary: EQT (EQT) has been quietly rewarding patient investors, with the stock up around 4% over the past week, 10% this month, and nearly 30% year to date as sentiment improves around natural gas. See our latest analysis for EQT. That steady climb in EQT’s share price, now around $61.17, reflects investors warming to natural gas leverage again, with a strong one year total shareholder return suggesting momentum is building rather than fading for now.
